SIMPLE: slattern
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slattern
<hw>Slat"tern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A woman who is
negligent of her dress or house; one who is not neat and nice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slattern</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slattern
<hw>Slat"tern</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Resembling a slattern; sluttish;
slatterny.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>slattern</xex> air.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Gay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slattern</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Slattern
<hw>Slat"tern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To consume
carelessly or wastefully; to waste; -- with <xex>away</xex>.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Chesterfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slatternliness</ent>⟦br⟧
